      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 105: The `generateServiceUuid` function now takes `std::mt19937_64\u0026` by non-const reference. This function is called from `SvcTunnelChannelHandler` which stores its own `rng_` member without any mutex protection (see svc_tunnel_channel_handler.h line 153). If `openTunnel` or `addService` can ever be called concurrently on the same object, the RNG state will be corrupted (data race / UB). The previous `thread_local` approach was inherently thread-safe. Verify that all call sites are single-threaded or add synchronization around RNG access.",
      "revId": "2fce5ffe3b01bb43d946515072862b004242ea2f",
