      "message": "Line 55: The `type` field accepts any string but the code only ever defaults to \"custom\". There is no validation that `type` is one of the documented values (\"custom\" or \"embedded\"). If an unknown type string is supplied (e.g. typo like \"embeded\"), it will be silently stored and persisted. Consider validating the value in `addService`/`updateService` or using an enum instead of a free-form string.",
