      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 60: The default for `localHost` changed from `\"127.0.0.1\"` to `\"localhost\"`. While functionally similar in most cases, `localhost` involves a DNS/hosts-file lookup and may resolve to `::1` (IPv6) on dual-stack systems, which could break services that only listen on IPv4 `127.0.0.1`. This is a behavioural change for existing deployments whose persisted JSON has no `localHost` key — `fromJson` will now default to `\"localhost\"` instead of `\"127.0.0.1\"`. Ensure this is intentional and that the TCP connect path handles both IPv4 and IPv6 resolution of `localhost`.",
      "revId": "2fce5ffe3b01bb43d946515072862b004242ea2f",
